All computations were performed with the Gaussian ’09, Revision B.01 software package (
Frisch et al., 2010
). Optimizations were carried in 
CH
2
Cl 
2
using the B3LYP functional. All atoms were described with the 6–311 + G(d,p) basis set (
Becke, 1993
; 
Lee et al., 1998
) with Polarizable Continuum Model (PCM) (
Tomasi et al., 2005
). Vibrational frequencies were computed at the same level of theory to verify that the optimized structures were minima.
